    <question>
        <prompt>The Adkins v. Children's Hospital decision reflected:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Support for worker protection</option>
            <option letter="b">Conservative support for business interests</option>
            <option letter="c">Progressive reform efforts</option>
            <option letter="d">Labor union influence</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The 1923 Adkins v. Children's Hospital decision reflected the Supreme Court's conservative support for business interests. By striking down a minimum wage law for women workers in Washington D.C., the Court demonstrated its commitment to "freedom of contract" and opposition to government regulation of business. This decision exemplified the pro-business orientation of the Supreme Court during the 1920s.</explanation>
    </question>
